[normal]The Chairman:[bold] Exactly. This is the point because with 28 member states I am sure there are going to be at least 40 different ideas, and some of them would be directly relevant to the problems that some other member state might have.
[normal]Max Uebe:[bold] We fully agree that there should be full transparency, but it is a problem that we have with the member states. When it comes to best practice and sharing, you might be aware of a range of what we call 
[normal]mutual learning programmes
